						               													<description>Mentsd meg a bolyg&amp;oacute;t (&amp;quot;Save the Planet&amp;quot;) is an environmental and ecological family board game in which you can learn how to become an active participant in the fight to save the Earth.&amp;#10;The mission cards ask the players to replace the polluting power plants on the world map with renewable energy plants.&amp;#10;The goal is to save our beautiful planet, and we can't help that better than by making children think.&amp;#10;Players must answer questions about energy, nature or the environment.&amp;#10;Event cards can not only help players, they can also cause unpleasant surprises and turn the tide of the game.&amp;#10;Example of questions for the cards:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     how much water do we lose on average per day due to a dripping tap? - 4 liters, or 9 liters, or 10 liters? (9 liters is the correct answer, which can be seen underlined on the card)&amp;#10;     which tree's fruit is edible? - chestnut, sweet chestnut, oak, beech, birch? (chestnut can be seen underlined)&amp;#10;     which of the following plants can help with orientation? - wild violet, nettle, moss, lace bush? (Moss)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Example of a mission card task:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     At least half of the power plants in Asia should be your wind farms!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A very beautiful, detailed world map board game for children and adults, which provides everyone with obtainable knowledge, new information, a new way of thinking, and adequate motivation to minimize the ecological footprint.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
